quran[5]{c,v,t,f}:
  24,54,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Obey<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Allah and obey the Messenger.” But if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>turn away, then he{1}is only responsible for what<i class=""s"">(duty) </i>he is made to carry, and you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are responsible for whatever<i class=""s"">(duty) </i>you are made to carry. For if you obey him, you will be guided, while the only responsibility of the Messenger is evident proclamation.",footnotes:1:The Prophet (peace be upon him).
  24,55,"Allah has promised those of you who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds that He will most surely make them successors in the land as <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Shu’ba read it as: “…as those before them were made successors (of others),”</span>,footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup> person to 1<sup><small>st</small></sup> person.
  24,56,"And establish<a class="sup"><sup>pl </sup></a>the prayer and bring{1}the purifying charity{2}and obey the Messenger, that you may be granted mercy.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.,footnotes:2:The Arabic word used is zakāt, which denotes purification and growth.
  24,57,"<span class=""h"">Never think</span><a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer and Hamza read it as: “Those who have denied should never think that they can thwart…”</span>
  24,58,"O you who have attained faith, let those whom you rightfully possess and those of you who have not reached puberty seek your <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Shu’ba, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…seek your permission (before entering). Three occasions…”</span>
